main event: A civilian observed a formation of four glowing white objects and one solitary object in the sky over Lutz, Florida on November 16, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were described as round to oval and bigger than average shooting stars., The initial sighting occurred at 0930Z and lasted for one and a half minutes., The formation was seen moving from north to east, while the solitary object was moving from east to west., The observer reported clear weather conditions during the sighting., The reliability of the observer was questioned due to his use of barbiturates for a toothache.
sighted object: four glowing white objects in formation and one solitary object
witness description: civilian, 25 years of age, carpenter, residing in a rural area
